articles.title: 1907, Feb 15
articles.content: The Gentlemen's Agreement between the United States and Japan results in the <highlight>prohibition of labor immigration</highlight> from Japan. Pres. Theodore Roosevelt issues an executive order halting immigration from Hawai'i, Mexico, and Canada to the U.S. mainland, to reduce Japanese immigration.
They don't think it be like it is, but it do
